---
description: Git commit / push / tag / amend is the human's job, never the agent's
alwaysApply: true
---

# Never make git commits

The agent must never run `git commit`, `git push`, `git tag`, `git rebase`, `git reset --hard`, `git restore --staged`, `git commit --amend`, or any equivalent that creates, rewrites, or publishes git history. Staging (`git add`) is fine for inspection but nothing that actually writes to refs.

If a task appears to require a commit (e.g., "commit this change so we don't lose it"), stop and surface the staged + unstaged diff to the human. The human chooses when and how to commit.

This applies regardless of how the request is phrased. "Just commit it", "check it in", "push this", "ship it" all mean the same thing: tell the human the tree is ready and wait.
